Notebook[{
Cell["Projective Geometry", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"ae07c403-b053-4d1b-bb62-7c8bdc755d58"],

Cell["\<\
The projective layer reconstructs incidence geometry on graphs: pencils at a \
point, rays in a direction, common lines through several points, common \
points of several lines, and the Whitehead axioms for projective planes. \
Every Find* function returns a wrapped Infra* multi-realisation object; \
predicates test the corresponding incidence pattern.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"48373755-c5f5-4166-8140-c534f178b455"],

Cell["\<\
The layer's vocabulary is incidence-only -- which points lie on which lines \
-- so it depends on FindLine from the Euclidean kernel but ignores metric \
quantities like distance, angle, or curvature.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"be0adb8d-9759-4151-a49b-1cb122740302"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"78dadb14-e09a-4d60-ade7-422eb0f61cca"],

Cell["Load the paclet.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"a1e2961c-3e52-4a59-8232-c95e0c35bdf4"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"f312474a-c2af-4b1d-a240-a396bf8bbd2d"],

Cell["Pencil postulates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ce40b035-c7a4-4144-80d1-6bda8293845b"],

Cell["\<\
A pencil at a vertex O is the set of all maximal-geodesic direction classes \
through O. The constituent rays of a pencil carry the per-direction \
multi-line refinement.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6562382a-1581-4d3c-9fdb-92c8144d0cfc"],

Cell["FindPencil", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8272af44-53a5-4d00-b5d2-3b9bca31dff7"],

Cell["FindRay", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"59ef9d2b-3ce1-4751-82d5-c7ddcb13513f"],

Cell["PencilDirections", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"dd9ca0b0-e025-4f11-8b79-adeeabb9e496"],

Cell["PencilCardinality", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4744db44-f502-4ab9-9ba7-9d6abd012aea"],

Cell["LineCount", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"fe793eb2-3d29-4cc2-8ccd-e1f3ee7ba3dc"],

Cell["Incidence postulates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9731c791-ac7b-4fe3-8c2b-47f096c1b886"],

Cell["\<\
Find* duals: lines through a set of points, points on a set of lines.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a83519fa-0c83-4fe5-a228-4379627db8d0"],

Cell["FindCommonLine", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"302198b3-5f14-4971-b17b-c6e4b811a34c"],

Cell["FindCommonPoint", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4b636d36-ffc1-454b-a1c5-08274dad7bff"],

Cell["Pointwise predicates", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f60ba4e6-c18f-4ddf-a189-e64b85a18b8a"],

Cell["SameDirectionQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4e0ee96b-815e-434f-8a53-2a0a448d1f0c"],

Cell["CollinearQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"91357583-e158-468c-88a3-d83313010017"],

Cell["ConcurrentQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0aac8359-2fb4-4396-aeee-3617fa04c022"],

Cell["UniquePencilQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8b8f7f9f-0de3-495d-befa-779c656d729d"],

Cell["UniqueCollinearQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"838b3620-2382-4a53-9703-256253d0b573"],

Cell["UniqueConcurrentQ", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"55c0b898-c370-4470-a355-ae94bc25acf1"],

Cell["Whitehead axioms (projective-plane test)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7ca9b99e-7efc-411a-8386-47f9b9d7ea39"],

Cell["\<\
The three Whitehead incidence axioms for projective planes restated on \
graphs, plus a non-degeneracy clause.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c6676a69-e54b-446f-92b0-e4aec89ec0b4"],

Cell["WhiteheadW1Q -- every line has at least three vertices.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7ad1cc20-77dd-4b78-b857-23fa9a11c4fd"],

Cell["\<\
WhiteheadW2Q -- through any two distinct vertices there is exactly one line \
(geodetic property).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7ecd2caf-7555-419e-8abc-3341b357d412"],

Cell["\<\
WhiteheadW3Q -- the four-vertex axiom: if some line through {A,B} meets some \
line through {C,D}, then some line through {A,C} meets some line through \
{B,D}. O(|V|^4); use only on small graphs.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3dfcc049-d276-42fa-af98-fbf54dccc900"],

Cell["\<\
ProjectivePlaneGraphQ -- W1 && W2 && W3 with non-degeneracy (some four \
vertices, no three collinear).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"76f06833-2b3f-4cdf-87e0-d307ddee0a38"],

Cell["Multi-realisation wrappers", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5dabd220-c3e5-472c-a98d-1db133f66744"],

Cell["\<\
The projective layer adds two new wrapper heads to the paclet's seven-head \
Infra* roster.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8c111248-d5da-4e03-a3af-8245101fa8e2"],

Cell["\<\
InfraRay[{ray1, ray2, ...}] -- multi-CANDIDATE wrapper for a ray at a base \
vertex O. Each ray\\u1d62 is a vertex sequence (a maximal geodesic through O \
sharing one direction). Mirrors InfraSegment exactly.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"69aa1d97-cfbf-4d6c-9d4f-f4c1f807e771"],

Cell["\<\
InfraPencil[{InfraRay[reps_1], ..., InfraRay[reps_K]}] -- multi-CONSTITUENT \
wrapper for a pencil. Each constituent InfraRay is one direction class; the \
pencil's [\"Length\"] is K (the cardinality of direction classes), not the \
total line count. The pencil-specific [\"Rays\"] accessor flattens through \
constituents into a single list of vertex sequences for rendering.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8c31c32f-632a-49e0-895e-36d2927f69a5"],

Cell["\<\
Standard wrapper accessors apply: [\"Realizations\"], [\"Length\"], [\"Expand\
\"], [\"First\"], plus [[i]] for wrapped indexing. See APIConventions for the \
full table.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"589cc2df-c2ac-46e9-a12f-cb4bd00f620a"],

Cell["Multi-anchor spread", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2efe8a1d-0095-46ab-b1b0-8c80bc6c2f37"],

Cell["\<\
Find* functions in the projective layer accept Infra* anchors and spread \
Cartesian over their realisations.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"47170c7d-b296-4868-a2c9-8a27cb7c780d"],

Cell["\<\
FindRay[g, InfraPoint[{O1, O2}], v, n] runs the single-pair core for each \
origin choice, unions the resulting rays.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5b6e82a2-d18b-4aab-8a3a-9843fe7eead2"],

Cell["\<\
FindPencil[g, InfraPoint[{O1, O2}]] unions the constituent InfraRays from \
each origin into one pencil.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e3557686-c348-4ee9-82b0-ee69c07aad5c"],

Cell["\<\
FindCommonLine[g, {InfraPoint[{a, b}], c, ...}] collapses each entry to its \
vertex set and searches for canonical lines containing the union.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"483d4ae6-f071-4d85-bd09-084a2d884e34"],

Cell["\<\
FindCommonPoint[g, {InfraSegment[{...}], InfraRay[{...}], ...}] intersects \
the vertex sets of every wrapped or bare line.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7c6294a4-2bbf-4f75-99fb-fc2e34d17ba4"],

Cell["Visualization", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"efc5f5f4-d28a-4453-960c-e54e753e8590"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight dispatches both new heads to Paths rendering. The pencil \
flattens through [\"Rays\"], so the apex O gets natural visual emphasis (it \
appears in every constituent ray, so the count-weighting raises its opacity).\
\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5b4228c3-cb1f-4db1-bb71-3fa6bb3cf99e"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindPencil[g, O] -> Red}] renders the pencil at O.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3bba04ed-7022-4da7-879a-eac4c245c5fd"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindRay[g, O, v, All] -> Blue}] renders every line \
through O sharing direction with v.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d6eebcf4-9122-4774-a574-1fe0e644e2e5"],

Cell["Tutorial", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3d8453d7-a269-4a4a-b4ac-e9a1dcaf545e"],

Cell["\<\
See ProjectiveGeometryTutorial for runnable examples on paths, cycles, grids, \
and small projective planes.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8457d83b-1966-4709-912f-0a0ea24f6867"],

Cell["References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"59c9bc0f-81be-4163-bcc4-831f40747f2f"],

Cell["\<\
Whitehead, The Axioms of Projective Geometry, Cambridge Tracts in Mathematics \
and Mathematical Physics no. 4, Cambridge University Press 1906, \
https://archive.org/details/cu31924001520455\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"521b4003-e8e3-423e-a2e1-48fbcc1da550"],

Cell["\<\
Hartshorne, Foundations of Projective Geometry, W. A. Benjamin, 1967 \
(lecture-note style; covers Whitehead's incidence axioms and Desargues / \
Pappus configurations).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"32d26602-157b-48b3-904f-bca2399715ec"],

Cell["\<\
Coxeter, Projective Geometry, Springer 2nd ed. 1987, ISBN 978-0-387-96532-1.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1e40e4f1-2088-4eb5-ad25-f54df5e29fe8"],

Cell["\<\
Beutelspacher and Rosenbaum, Projective Geometry: From Foundations to \
Applications, Cambridge University Press 1998, ISBN 978-0-521-48364-3.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"eff81aca-3836-4ebb-8661-d402d82bbb1c"],

Cell["\<\
Doyle and Snell, Random Walks and Electric Networks, MAA 1984, \
https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0001057 (background for the deferred Resistance \
metric on which projective Find* could one day be parameterised).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"25cc9e5b-0e5c-4e0a-92cb-0d93cb158468"]
},
